reviews.review: WELL DONE JJ Abrams! GREAT TRANSITION from the very first episodes tying in to the FINAL SAGA. YOU WILL LOVE this final movie IF YOU ARE A TRUE STAR WARS FAN!!! JJA did an excellent job tying everything together without being over the top. If you haven't seen the entire first 8 episodes, watch it, then watch this.
I don't know why the rating is so low for this movie. I loved it and think it ranks up there as one of the best star wars films of all time.

As a lifelong SW fan I have been excited for this movie for a long time, despite being quite disappointed about the past two sequels. Where The Last Jedi really lacked in story I personally believe this movie really connected ALL 9 movies together with a satisfying and emotionally stimulating ending. No one can argue that visually, the movie is outstanding. The story is undeniably, quite complex. It could well have been split into two but due to the awkward situation of the last movie not going down well with most fans, JJ had to really make this a capturing story whilst cramming a crap ton of plot into it. For anyone who is a big fan of the franchise this should be a very satisfying end to the saga plus for those, like me, who felt the sequels lacked character depth - this movie does help you enjoy TFA & TLJ more knowing what we do about the characters and their background at the end of ROTS. Just keep in mind, it'll never really "feel like a Star Wars movie" the way the originals did. Instead its a refreshing, new take on the movie whilst still sticking to the fundamentals of the franchise the fans love (John Williams proves himself as an incredible composer once again for example!)
Between the agenda(identity politics) they just couldn't leave out of this movie to the fast paced, awful acting, this movie is a dumpster fire. Glad the trilogy is over. Boring movie.
